
[1]remarkably

   REM'ARKABLY, adv.

   1. In a manner or degree worthy of notice; as, the winters of 1825,
   1826 and 1828 were remarkably free from snow. The winter of 1827 was
   remarkable for a great quantity of snow.

   2. In an extraordinary manner.
